Package com.sixbank.notificationlibrary.shared.events

Class NotificationDeliveredEvent

java.lang.Object
com.sixbank.notificationlibrary.shared.events.base.BaseEvent
com.sixbank.notificationlibrary.shared.events.NotificationDeliveredEvent
All Implemented Interfaces:
DomainEvent
public class NotificationDeliveredEvent extends BaseEvent
Domain event fired when a notification has been successfully delivered to the recipient.

This event captures details about the delivery channel, provider used, timestamp of delivery, delivery attempt count, and any external system identifiers.

Usage Example:

 NotificationDeliveredEvent event = new NotificationDeliveredEvent(
     "notif-1234",
     "customer-5678",
     ChannelType.EMAIL,
     "SendGrid",
     Instant.now(),
     1,
     "external-message-id-9876"
 );

This event can be published after the notification service confirms delivery, enabling downstream systems to track notification status and analytics.

      public NotificationDeliveredEvent(String notificationId, String customerId, ChannelType channelType, String provider, Instant deliveredAt, int attemptNumber, String externalId)
      Constructs a NotificationDeliveredEvent with delivery details.
      Parameters:
      notificationId - Unique identifier for the notification (aggregateId).
      customerId - Identifier for the customer who received the notification.
      channelType - Delivery channel used (e.g., EMAIL, SMS).
      provider - Name of the external provider or service used for delivery.
      deliveredAt - Timestamp when the notification was delivered.
      attemptNumber - Number of attempts taken to deliver this notification.
      externalId - External system ID referencing the delivered message.
